content:
The standard HTTP API provides this pretty easily (lighthouse and teku support this, I think nimbus does as well, prysm are working on it):

```
curl -s 'localhost:5052/eth/v1/beacon/states/head/validators?id=12345' | jq
{
  "data": [
    {
      "index": "12345",
      "balance": "32069196072",
      "status": "active_ongoing",
      "validator": {
        "pubkey": "0xb2939a65b7e8e01107b3ac95106f8b425b3390819912fe30a3ae30b72716a467a17360031de4a77880c33b71de8d9fa5",
        "withdrawal_credentials": "0x007dafca49b2f7a87a36da58e1c57551a5eb776799011c5730b21d6e650b2ceb",
        "effective_balance": "32000000000",
        "slashed": false,
        "activation_eligibility_epoch": "0",
        "activation_epoch": "0",
        "exit_epoch": "18446744073709551615",
        "withdrawable_epoch": "18446744073709551615"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```
